column95:
UCL WILL MANAGE TASK 3 OF THIS PROJECT TITLED   EVALUATE CURRENT THREAT ASSESSMENTS AND THREAT MANAGEMENT - TEST EFFICACY   
 
 THIS PART OF THE PROJECT SYNTHESISES THE KNOWLEDGE BASE ON WHAT WORKS IN THREAT
 ASSESSMENT THROUGH THE USE OF SYSTEMATIC REVIEW AND META-ANALYSIS. RATHER THAN ASKING 'DOES THREAT ASSESSMENT WORK', IT ASKS 'HOW CAN THREAT ASSESSMENT WORK, FOR WHOM, ON WHOM, AND IN WHAT CIRCUMSTANCES'. BY SYNTHESISING THE EXISTING KNOWLEDGE IN THIS WAY, WE CAN ARTICULATE THE CONTEXTUAL FACTORS WHICH CONTRIBUTE TOWARD THE SUCCESS, OR NOT, OF DIFFERENT THREAT ASSESSMENT
 MODALITIES (E.G. REMOTE VS. IN-PERSON ASSESSMENTS; UP-STREAM PREVENTION VS. RECIDIVISIM; VIOLENT EXTREMISM VS. INSIDER THREAT VS. GENERAL VIOLENCE).

column56: THE PURPOSE OF THIS ORDER IS TO PROCURE THE SERVICES OF ERG TO PERFORM THE DUTIES AS OUTLINED IN THE CONFLICT PREVENTION AND RESOLUTION CENTER JUST IN TIME DISPUTE RESOLUTION PROJECTS SOW. THIS ORDER ALSO INCORPORATES THE APPROVED WORK PLAN AND COST
column59: ALL OTHER PROFESSIONAL, SCIENTIFIC, AND TECHNICAL SERVICES
column95: SUBCONTRACTORS UNDER THIS CONTRACT MAY PERFORM A VARIETY OF ALTERNATIVE DISPUTE RESOLUTION (ADR) SERVICES, INCLUDING MEDIATING DISPUTES WITHIN EPA OR WITH EXTERNAL STAKEHOLDERS, FACILITATING MEETINGS, DEVELOPING AND DELIVERING TRAINING, PROVIDING ORGANIZATIONAL DEVELOPMENT AND INDIVIDUALIZED COACHING SUPPORT TO HELP EPA MANAGERS AND TEAMS WORK MORE EFFECTIVELY TOGETHER, AND PROMOTING ENGAGEMENT WITH COMMUNITIES AROUND CHALLENGING ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES. SUBCONTRACTOR TASKS MAY INCLUDE PLANNING, CONVENING PARTIES, DELIVERING ADR SERVICES, AND EVALUATING AND REPORTING OUTCOMES.

column95: SUBCONTRACTORS UNDER THIS CONTRACT MAY PERFORM A VARIETY OF ALTERNATIVE DISPUTE RESOLUTION (ADR) SERVICES, INCLUDING MEDIATING DISPUTES WITHIN EPA OR WITH EXTERNAL STAKEHOLDERS, FACILITATING MEETINGS, DEVELOPING AND DELIVERING TRAINING, PROVIDING ORGANIZATIONAL DEVELOPMENT AND INDIVIDUALIZED COACHING SUPPORT TO HELP EPA MANAGERS AND TEAMS WORK MORE EFFECTIVELY TOGETHER, AND PROMOTING ENGAGEMENT WITH COMMUNITIES AROUND CHALLENGING ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES. column95:
THIS EFFORT SEEKS TO CONDUCT RESEARCH TO FULLY UNDERSTAND AND SUPPORT HOW HUMAN BEHAVIOR AFFECTS POSITIVE SAFETY AND SECURITY OUTCOMES IN VARIOUS THREAT SCENARIOS, SPECIFICALLY COUNTERING IMPROVISED EXPLOSIVE DEVICE (CIED) EVENTS AND OTHER THREAT SCENARIOS FACING THE INFRASTRUCTURE SECURITY COMMUNITY.
 OVER THE YEARS, RESEARCH HAS SHOWN THAT THERE ARE OVERLAPPING REQUIREMENTS WHEN IT COMES TO HOW ONE WOULD BETTER UNDERSTAND THE IDENTIFICATION OF SUSPICIOUS BEHAVIOR IN TARGETED VIOLENCE AND TERRORISM PREVENTION TO THOSE SEEKING TO IMPACT PUBLIC SAFETY THROUGH THE DETONATION OF AN IED IN ONE OF OUR KEY CRITICAL INFRASTRUCTURE SECTORS.
